1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Chevy Control here again.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Earlier in the flight, you'll recall, at the start of the Second Revolution,

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
we had a reference to several objects that the crew spotted.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
This was in the area of Antigua.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Due to a mechanical breakdown, we did not have that portion of the tape available for you.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:33,000
This was a line breakdown between Building 30 and our new center in Building 6.

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Since then, we have dubbed the tape off the master tape here in the control center,

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
and we are now prepared to play it for you.

9
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:48,000
It contains references to sighting not only some particles,

10
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
but as well as an unidentified object,

11
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
plus the booster.

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Here's that tape. We'll play it for you now.

13
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Gemini 7 here, Houston on your 8.

14
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Loud and clear. 7, go ahead.

15
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Bogey at 10 o'clock high.

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
This is Houston. Say again, 7.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
So we have a bogey at 10 o'clock high.

18
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Roger.

19
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Roger.

20
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Gemini 7, is that the booster, or is that an actual sighting?

21
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Not working.

22
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Say again, 7.

23
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Roger.

24
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:47,000
We have several, looks like a three up there, actual sighting.

25
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Do you have any more information, estimated distance or size?

26
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Roger.

27
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
We also have the booster in sight.

28
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Understand you also have the booster in sight.

29
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Roger.

30
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:06,000
And we have very, very many, looks like hundreds of little particles going by from the west,

31
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,000
going by from the west, out about three to four miles.

32
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:21,000
Understand you have many small particles going by on the left, at what distance?

33
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Four miles.

34
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Roger.

35
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Looks like a, perhaps a vehicle that's disintegrated.

36
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Roger.

37
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Understand they're about three to four miles away.

38
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,000
They're past now.

39
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,000
They're going to pull a little bit.

40
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Roger.

41
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,000
And understand they were about three to four miles away.

42
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Roger.

43
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Roger.

44
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Roger.

45
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Roger.

46
00:02:44,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Gemini 7 Houston, were these particles in addition to the booster and the bogey at 10 o'clock

47
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,000
high?

48
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Command.

49
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,000
Roger.

50
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Uh, 7, this is, uh, Houston, this is 7.

51
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Go ahead.

52
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
I have the, uh, booster on my side.

53
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:19,000
It's a brilliant body of the sun, just a back, uh, black background.

54
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:23,000
There's a brilliant particles around it.

55
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Roger.

56
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,000
What direction is it from you?

57
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,000
It's about at my two o'clock position.

58
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Does that mean it's ahead of you?

59
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,000
It's ahead of us, 2 o'clock, slowly doubling.

60
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Roger.

61
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Roger.

62
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Roger.

63
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Roger.

64
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Roger.

65
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Roger.

66
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Roger.

67
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:10,920
4S-9-1.

68
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:57,000
4S-9-1.

69
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:04,000
5S-9-1.

70
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:08,000
5S-9-1.

71
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:16,000
5S-9-1.

72
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:25,000
7S-9-1.

73
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Show me control here again.

74
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:38,000
The reference in that conversation to the third unidentified object, of course, was, or the third object was a bogie.

75
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:58,340
There were several references to the bogey. This is the unidentified object, in addition to particles which appear to be headed in a polar orbit, you heard Frank Borman say, plus Jim Lovell discussing the booster. It was Borman who reported sighting the bogey.

76
00:05:59,780 --> 00:06:05,140
This is Germany Control in Houston at four hours, 24 minutes into the flight.

77
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:37,980
